HEADWORD: beret
<hw>beret</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a cap made of soft cloth with no brim
or bill, widening somewhat outward from a close-fitting headband to a
flat top, which often has a button or tab in its center.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

